<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Rare, Old Books On Show In New Delhi </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 26 (Xinhua) -- A show of over 1,000 rare
and old books on various subjects published before 1900 was opened
here on Saturday by Congress President Sonia Gandhi.
</P>
<P>
The five-day exhibition at the Nehru Memorial Museum and
Library has a separate section on the "War of Independence" in
1857 with some 30 titles including "Campaign in India from 1857-58
from drawings made during the eventful period of Great Mutiny"
published in 1859.
</P>
<P>
The oldest volume on display was published in 1777, which
contained the original papers of the Nabob of Arcot.
</P>
<P>
Other notable books include Proceedings of the first Indian
National Congress published in 1885, "Annexation of Punjab" by
Evans Bell (1882) and the Great Wahabi Case (1888).
</P>
<P>
The books were culled from the Nehru Library's collection of
over 200,000 publications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
