<HEADLINE> Xinhua Photo List for February 26 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Following is the photo list
for February 26.
</P>
<P>
1. Festooned vehicles move in the main street of Nanjing,
capital city of Jiangsu Province, during the opening parade of the
International Plum Blossom Festival on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
2. Girl speedskater Lou Shijia (front) dashes to title the
female group-two competition during the First National Junior
Short Track Speedskating, which began on Saturday in Shenyang,
capital of northeast China's Liaoning Province. 232 teen skaters
from all over China take part in the two-day-long contest.
</P>
<P>
3. Teen skater Wang Yong in action during the male group-one
competition of the First National Short Track Speedskating Contest,
which began on February 26 in Shenyang, capital city of China's
northeast Liaoning Province.
</P>
<P>
4. Children paint their dreams for safe and jamless traffic on
a 100-meter-long canvas in Ji'nan, capital city of east China's
Shandong Province, on February 26. A project called "Traffic
without Jams" is launched on the same day in 36 cities all over
China.
</P>
<P>
5. A foreign staff member at the French booth explains to
Chinese girl students about how to study in French universities
during the International Higher Education Exhibition which starts
on February 26 in Beijing. Some 160 universities from 16 countries,
including the United States, Canada and France are represented at
the exhibition.
</P>
<P>
6. A British teacher helps a Chinese student with spoken
English in a simulated classroom during the International Higher
Education Exhibition on February 26 in Beijing.
</P>
<P>
7. Li Peng, Chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, meets with Vietnamese Foreign Minister
Nguyen Dy Nien at the Great Hall of the People in Beijing on
February 26.
</P>
<P>
8. Li Peng, Chairman of the Standing Committee of the Chinese
National People's Congress, shakes hands with a woman worker at
Sunlight Woollen Mill on February 26 in Jiangyin, east China's
Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
9. 8-year-old Ma Yuchen points to her painting titled "Windmill
in the Netherlands" and explains to her mother at the ongoing
exhibition "Europe in My Eyes" on February 26, in Beijing. On
display are the works of 17 children age 6-13 created after their
trips to European countries.
</P>
<P>
10. A girl student raises hand for help during the 1st National
Computer Exam for Teens held on February 26 in Beijing. The
examinees are encouraged to be creative and allowed to discuss
with each other and ask for help from their teachers during the
exam.  
</P>
