<HEADLINE> Romanian Wins Women's 1,500m Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GENT, Belgium, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Violeta Szekely put her
country Romania on the gold medal podium on Saturday at the
European Indoor Athletic Championships by winning the women's 1,
500-meter race.
</P>
<P>
The Romanian distance runner clocked four minutes 12.82 seconds
over the distance while Olga Kuznetsova and Yulia Kosenkova picked
up the silver and bronze medals for Russia as they finished second
and third in the event.
</P>
<P>
The Russian duo were timed 4:13.45 and 4:13.60 respectively.
</P>
<P>
Liubov Kremlyova also from Russia was not medal lucky and did
not finish the race at all.
</P>
<P>
Following are the results for the finalists of the women's 1,
500-meter race:
</P>
<P>
1. Violeta Szekely, Romania, 4 minutes 12.82 seconds -- gold
medal
</P>
<P>
2. Olga Kuznetsova, Russia, 4:13.45 -- silver medal
</P>
<P>
3. Yulia Kosenkova, Russia, 4:13.60 -- bronze medal
</P>
<P>
4. Sinead Delahunty, Ireland, 4:15.87
</P>
<P>
5. P. Djate-Taillard, France, 4:17.69
</P>
<P>
6. D. Briand-Calenic, France, 4:18.70
</P>
<P>
7. Aysen Barak, Turkey, 4:19.21
</P>
<P>
Liubov Kremlyova, Russia, did not finish
</P>
<P>
Kathleen Friedrich, Germany, did not finish
</P>
</TEXT>
