<HEADLINE> Serbian Police Ambushed by Kosovo Albanian Terrorists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BELGRADE, February 27 (Xinhua) -- A Serbian policeman was
killed and three others injured Saturday night when they were
ambushed by Kovovo Albanian terrorists during a patrol mission,
the Tanjug news agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Citing a press release issued by the Serbian Interior Ministry
Sunday, the report said that the terrorists attacked a police team
with automatic weapons and grenades on the highway to the western
Kosovar city of Gnjilane.
</P>
<P>
The police fought back and killed a terrorist, who was a member
of the Kosovo protection Corps (KPC) in Gnjilane, it said.
</P>
<P>
Last November, two Serb policemen were killed when their
vehicle hit a mine laid by Kovoso Albanian terrorists on a road
section near Prepolac. 
</P>
