<HEADLINE> British Driver Takes Kenya's Safari Rally </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- British driver Richard Burns
took the title at Kenya's 47th Safari Rally on Sunday, followed by
defeating runner-up Juha Kankkunen of Finland in four minutes, 37
seconds in Kenya.
</P>
<P>
Didier Auriol of France was third in the three-day race across
central Kenya, trailing 22:44 behind the leader.
</P>
<P>
Burns, driving a Subaru Impreza WRC, led Kankkunen, also
driving an Impreza, by 4:55 entering the final day of the 2,691-
kilometer race.
</P>
<P>
Only few of the original 46 starters raced in Saturday's field.
Fourteen vehicles withdrew, including defending champion Colin
McRae and Marcus Gronholm, who were forced out with transmission
problems.
</P>
<P>
The rally is third in the 14 series of World Championship
circuit and counts for both drivers and manufacturers awards.
</P>
<P>
The Kenya race began in 1953 to celebrate the coronation of
Queen Elizabeth II, when Kenya was still a British colony.
</P>
</TEXT>
