<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Syrian Paper Rebukes Jospin's Controversial Remarks </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAMASCUS, February 27 (Xinhua) -- A newspaper of Syria's ruling
Baath Arab Socialist Party on Sunday commented on the statements
made by French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin, accusing them of
triggering a violent shock throughout the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The daily Baath pointed out that the statements are
contradicting the balanced moderate foreign policy France has been
adopting towards the Middle East and are regarded as a violation of
principles in international relations.
</P>
<P>
In statements made during his visit to Israel, Jospin described
the attacks launched by Hezbollah guerrillas in southern Lebanon to
end Israeli occupation there as "terrorist" acts.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian paper said that Jospin took an entirely biased
attitude in favor of Israel and denied Lebanon's legitimate right
in resisting and fighting against the Israeli forces occupying
southern Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
The paper added that Jospin forgot the fact that he represented
a great country which has always sought to adopt positive positions
in supporting the legitimate rights of countries and nations.
</P>
<P>
Syrian Foreign Ministry on Saturday summoned the French
ambassador in Damascus to protest against Jospin's controversial
statements, and ask for official clarifications. 
</P>
</TEXT>
