<HEADLINE> HK's Financial Sector Prepared for Y2K Leap-Year Date Rollover </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The financial services
sector of Hong Kong is well prepared for the Y2K leap-year date
change.
</P>
<P>
"The Financial Sector Emergency Co-ordination Center (FSECC)
set up by the Financial Services Bureau will come into operation
in the evening of February 28," a spokesman of the center said
Sunday.
</P>
<P>
Also to be activated at the same time are the Y2K event
management or command centers of major Hong Kong financial
organizations, including the Hong Kong Monetary Authority, the
Securities and Futures Commission, the Office of the Commission of
Insurance, the Stock Exchange of Hong Kong, Hong Kong Futures
Exchange, Hong Kong Securities Clearing Company and Hong Kong
Interbank Clearing Limited.
</P>
<P>
"The FSECC will work very closely with these centers to monitor
the situation in the financial services sector and developments
overseas during the leap-year date change," the spokesman added.
</P>
<P>
The FSECC and the other centers are expected to continue their
operation up to March 1. 
</P>
