<HEADLINE> Pro-Israeli Militiaman Injured in South Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIRUT, February 27 (Xinhua) -- A militiaman of the pro-Israeli
South Lebanon Army (SLA) was injured Sunday in a roadside bomb
attack by Lebanese guerrillas in the Israeli-occupied zone in
southern Lebanon, security sources said.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian- and Syrian-backed Hezbollah, or Party of God, has
claimed responsibility for the attack on the Khardaly bridge in the
eastern sector of the "security zone," which brought to 12 the
number of SLA members wounded in the region since the beginning of
the year.
</P>
<P>
Seven Israeli soldiers have been killed in the occupation zone
in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Hezbollah has been leading a guerrilla war to oust Israeli
troops and SLA militiamen from southern Lebanon, where Israel
carved out a buffer zone in 1985 with the claimed aim to protect
its northern territory. 
</P>
