<HEADLINE> Six Indian Soldiers Reportedly Killed In Kashmir </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- India said that Pakistan
attacked one of its early warning post on Sunday in Naushera
sector of the disputed Kashmir, killing at least six Indian
soldiers.
</P>
<P>
Official sources at the Defense Ministry said here today that
the post, surrounded on three sides by Pakistani army positions
across the so-called line of control (LOC), was raided by
Pakistani forces at 0430 hours local time (1000 GMT).
</P>
<P>
While six Indian soldiers were killed in the raid, one junior
commissioned officer and one other rank were missing along with
their weapons, the sources said.
</P>
<P>
The post has been used to monitor movement of Pakistani troops
and militants along the LOC in the area.
</P>
<P>
However, the sources said, the losses on the Pakistani side
could not be immediately known.
</P>
<P>
This is reportedly the third major flare-up in the area in
recent weeks. Last month, 18 Pakistani soldiers were killed when
they tried to capture an Indian border post in an area adjacent to
Naushera, according to Indian media.
</P>
<P>
Earlier this month, five Pakistani soldiers and four Indian
army troops were reportedly killed during the fire exchange
between the two sides in Akhnoor sector of Kashmir.
</P>
<P>
However, official sources here denied reports from Islamabad
that Indian troops crossed the LOC last Friday and killed at least
Pakistani civilians. 
</P>
</TEXT>
