<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0080 GMT, February 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUENOS AIRES -- The number of privately owned weapons in
Argentina has almost quintupled from 400,000 in 1993 to 1.938
million, authorities said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The National Weapons Registry said in its latest report that 60
percent of all of the weapons registered are privately owned, 25
percent are controlled by members of the armed forces and security
agencies, and the rest are used by employees of security firms or
are kept by collectors. (Argentine-Firearms)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
WASHINGTON -- U.S. authorities Saturday expelled a Cuban
diplomat ignoring an expulsion order and put him on a flight bound
for Montreal, Canada, where he will be flown to Cuba's capital
Havana.
</P>
<P>
The diplomat, Jose Imperatori, earlier Saturday announced he
went on a hunger strike to protest the U.S. expulsion order.
</P>
<P>
"The diplomat in question no longer enjoys the privileges and
immunities conferred by the Vienna Convention on Diplomatic
Relations," the U.S. State Department said in a written statement.
(US-Cuba-Diplomat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- India's inflation rate dropped to a 20-week low of
2.37 percent for the week ended on February 12,2000, on account of
sharp decline in prices of primary articles.
</P>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, the 0.19 percentage
points fall in the annual rate of inflation to 2.37 percent from 2.
56 percent in the previous week was triggered by the decline in
the Index of Primary Articles and manufacturing products. (India-
Inflation) 
</P>
</TEXT>
