<HEADLINE> Lack of Wind Postpones 4th Race of America's Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WELLINGTON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The fourth race of the
America's Cup finals series in Auckland, the biggest city of New
Zealand, was postponed Sunday due to lack of wind.
</P>
<P>
Race organizers delayed the start by more than two hours, but
called off the race when stronger winds failed to materialize.
</P>
<P>
The fourth race will now be held on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Team New Zealand is leading the best of nine series by three
races to nil over the Italian boat Prada.  
</P>
</TEXT>
