<HEADLINE> Hardaway Inspires Heat to Victory over Wizards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Tim Hardaway scored seven
of his 23 points in a fourth-quarter 10-2 run to inspire the Miami
Heat to a 98-88 victory over the Washington Wizards here on
Saturday.
</P>
<P>
"Tim was vintage tonight," said Heat coach Pat Riley. Hardaway
hit 4-of-6 shots from 3-point range and made all five of his free
throws.
</P>
<P>
Miami centre Alonzo Mourning scored 28 points, making 12-of-13
from the line, and blocked three shots.
</P>
<P>
Tracy Murray scored 20 points off the bench for Washington,
which has lost its last seven meetings with Miami.
</P>
<P>
In other games, Indiana beat Golden State 104-88, New Jersey
swept past Charlotte 104-93, while Dallas beat Denver 98-96.
</P>
<P>
Vancouver rolled over Sacramento 102-90 and Los Angeles
Clippers won over Atlanta 78-77. 
</P>
