<HEADLINE> Inflation Drops to 2.37 pct in India </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
According to the Reserve Bank of India, the 0.19 percentage
fall in the annual rate of inflation to 2.37 percent from 2.56
percent in the previous week was triggered by the decline in the
Index of Primary Articles and manufacturing products.
</P>
<P>
However, the country's inflation was higher at 5.12 percent
during the corresponding week in 1999.
</P>
<P>
After rising to a 32-week high of 3.31 percent for the week on
January 22, 2000, the inflation rate has been steadily falling due
to decline in prices of various primary articles. 
</P>
