<HEADLINE> Slovenia's Kunc Takes First World Cup Title </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SEOUL, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Slovenia's Mitja Kunc on Sunday
took his first World Cup slalom title after overtaking first-run
leader Ole Kristian Furuseth of Norway in a race in Yongpyong,
South Korea.
</P>
<P>
Kunc, whose best previous results were seconds in giant slaloms
in 1994 and 1995, registered a total time of one minute, 31.97
seconds for the victory.
</P>
<P>
Furuseth, the 1998 Yongpyong winner who led the first run by a
10th of a second, was runner-up in 1:32.70.  Mario Matt of
Austria took the third place in 1:32.97.  
