<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 340 Kilos of Drug Material Seized in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The Myanmar authorities seized
a total of 340 kilos of ephedrine powder, a kind of raw material
used in producing amphetamine stimulant drugs, in the country's
second largest city of Mandalay early this month, official
newspaper The New Light of Myanmar reported Sunday.
</P>
<P>
The seizure was made by a combined team of the local
intelligence unit and police force when they searched the houses
of five local people in Mandalay's four townships on February 8
and 9.
</P>
<P>
Action is being taken against the five drug traffickers under
Myanmar's Narcotic Drugs and Psychotropic Substances Law, the
report said.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, Myanmar seized 6,336 kilos of
ephedrine along with 28.75 million tablets of stimulant drugs in
the country in 1999.
</P>
<P>
Stimulant drugs were first found trafficked in Myanmar in 1996.
In the past four years, the authorities have confiscated a total
of 55.89 million tablets of stimulant drugs in the country.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
