<HEADLINE> Tourism Boom for Jiangxi During Spring Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The tourism industry boomed
in east China's Jiangxi Province during this year's Spring
Festival holiday season which began on February 5.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that the number of tourists to the province
reached more than 400,000 in the festival period, an all-time high.
</P>
<P>
Jiangxi, a province rich in tourism resources, presented many
activities to attract tourists this year. One tourist route from
Nanchang, capital of the province, to Bangkok in Thailand
attracted a large numbers of visitors, as seventeen travel
agencies in Nanchang united as one to provide first-rate service.
</P>
<P>
Lushan Mountain, a World Culture Heritage site, increased its
reception capacity by 30 percent, as many people went there to see
the snow. The renowned "porcelain capital" of Jingdezhen and the
Jinggang Mountains, a cradle of the Chinese revolutions also
played host to many tourist groups. 
</P>
