<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 0100 GMT, February 27 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Russian Security Council, the country's top
security policy agency, Friday made a decision to establish
interim administration in coming days and to restore economy in
the liberated parts of the rebel republic of Chechnya as soon as
possible.
</P>
<P>
Russian Central Election Commission Chairman Alexander
Veshnyakov plans to visit Chechnya to acquaint himself with the
preparations for the March 26 Russian presidential elections in
the republic, Security Council Secretary Sergei Ivanov said after
Friday's council session chaired by Acting Russian President
Vladimir Putin.
</P>
<P>
In coming two weeks the government will complete the
preparation for a measure program on restoring the power
structures and the social and economic sectors in Chechnya, Ivanov
predicted.
</P>
<P>
To organize new power structures, "a transitional period will
be required, since now it is unrealistic to set up in Chechnya
republican power similar to that in other federal territories,"
Ivanov said, noting that he regards this as "an issue for long-
term discussion." (Russia-Chechnya-Plan)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
HAVANA -- Cuban diplomat Jose Imperatori in the United States
resigned the post and started a hunger strike on Saturday in
protest against an accusation of spying.
</P>
<P>
The deadline given on February 19 by the U.S.Department of
State to Imperatori to leave the United States, after being
charged with alleged links of spying for the island with Mariano
Faget, an Immigration and Naturalization Service (INS) official,
comes due Saturday.
</P>
<P>
The Cuban government announced that it would ask its diplomat
to remain in Washington to demonstrate the fallacy of the
accusation, whatever the consequences.
</P>
<P>
"My decision is voluntary. I do not belong anymore to the
Office of Interests. I will assume the responsibility and the
consequences," said Imperatori in a letter entitled "To the United
States people," published in this capital.
</P>
<P>
He said he will remain in the apartment where he has been
living and in hunger strike, until the accusation is completely
cleared."I will not resist if I am arrested, if I am manacled and
if I am jailed," he said.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Department of State spokesman James Rubin said
Tuesday that if the Cuban representative does not go, he will lose
his immunity and will be subjected to U.S. laws. "If there are
reasons to arrest him, he will be arrested," said Rubin. (US-Cuba-
Diplomat)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
PARIS -- French Prime Minister Lionel Jospin returned to Paris
Saturday evening from his visit to Israel and the Palestinian
autonomous territories, which was marked by a violent attack upon
him by Palestinian demonstrators.
</P>
<P>
Jospin was injured in his head by a stone thrown by the
Palestinians at the University of Bir Zeit in the West Bank
Saturday morning.
</P>
<P>
The attack took place after Jospin said on Thursday in
Jerusalem that the attacks upon Israeli troops by Hezbollah
guerrillas in southern Lebanon were acts of terrorism.
</P>
<P>
When he ended a visit to the University of Bir Zeit, Jospin was
attacked by a rainfall of stones from Palestinian students who
surrounded him and his delegation members, including French
Foreign Minister Hubert Vedrine.
</P>
<P>
His car was seriously damaged after being stoned and kicked for
several minutes by violent demonstrators, who blocked the exit
route of the motorcade of Jospin's.
</P>
<P>
Jospin cut short his visit to the Palestinians territories and
cancelled a visit to a refugee camp and a joint press conference
with Palestinian leader Yasser Arafat.
</P>
<P>
Before he left Israel for home, Israeli Prime Minister Ehud
Barak called Jospin and expressed his support and salutation. (
France-Jospin-Trip) 
</P>
</TEXT>
