<HEADLINE> hke - Skjelbreid Takes Second Gold Medal at Worlds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
STOCKHOLM, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Liv Grete Skjelbreid won the
women's 12.5-kilometer event to take her second gold medal on
Saturday at the World Biathlon Championships held in Oslo, Norway.
</P>
<P>
The Norwegian's fiance Raphael Poiree also won the individual
race of the men's 15-kilometer.
</P>
<P>
Skjelbreid, who plans to marry Poiree after the season, won
the women's event 13.4 seconds ahead of Russia's Galian Kukleva.
Both had two misses on thge shooting range.
</P>
<P>
Skjelbreid, winner of 7.5k a week ago, crossed the finish line
at famous Holmenkollen before a boisterous, flag-waving crowd of
some 30,000 in 38 minutes, 51.7 seconds.
</P>
<P>
Corinne Niogret of France was third Saturday, 23.6 seconds
back.
</P>
<P>
Poiree clocked 39:31.5 in the men's 15K. The Frenchman had one
miss. Pavel Rostovtsev of Russia took the silver, 9.4 seconds back.
The bronze medal went to Ole Einar Bjorndalen of Norway, 18.4
seconds behind.
</P>
<P>
Poiree now leads Bjorndalen 411 points to 383 in the World cup
standings. 
</P>
</TEXT>
