<HEADLINE> American Bergoust Wins His First World Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
ROME, February 26 (Xinhua) -- American Eric Bergoust scored
his first freestyle World Cup victory of the season Saturday when
he defeated overall co-leaders Nicolas Fontaine and Alexei Grichin
in an aerials event held in Piancavallo, Italy.
</P>
<P>
Australian Jacqui Cooper dominated the women's aerials for her
fourth victory of the season increased her lead in the World Cup
standings.
</P>
<P>
Bergoust won the men's event ahead of Canada's Steve Omischl
and fellow-American Joe Pack with 257.21 points.
</P>
<P>
Fontaine, a Canadian, and Grichin, of Belarus, finished fourth
and sixth respectively, putting them in a tie atop the standings
with 376 points.
</P>
<P>
Pack was third with 360 and Bergoust a distant 12th, at 216.
</P>
<P>
Cooper scored 185.54 points, beating Canada's Veronica Brenner
's 177.51 in the women's event and increasing her overall point
total to 400, 24 ahead of Brenner. 
</P>
