<HEADLINE> Olano Wins 20-kilometer Time Trial </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Spain's Abraham Olano captured
the five-day Tour of Valencia on Saturday by winning 20-kilometer
time trial.
</P>
<P>
Olano, among a contingent of eight riders who started the day
two seconds behind the overall leader after Friday's fourth stage _
Giuseppe di Grande of Italy, Olano finished the 20-kilometer(12-
mile time trial in and around this eastern coastal city in 24
minutes, 18 seconds, according to reports reaching here.
</P>
<P>
Compatriots Juan Carlos Dominguez and Jose Alberto Martinez,
who also were in the pack of eight, were second and third in
Saturday's time trial and finished in those respective places in
the final overall standings, 21 and 47 seconds behind Olano.
</P>
<P>
Di Grande finished the race in eighth place 1:48 behind Olano,
while Jalabert, finished the stage 10th and wound up fifth in the
overall standings 1:12 behind Olano. 
</P>
