<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Enthusiastic about Development of Western China (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The association will also carry out scientific education
project in western China over the next five years, setting up 100
showcase educational centers and 100 farming technology societies
there. It will also use its wide connections to introduce
outstanding talent to the west.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese media have stirred up waves of publicity about the
development of the region, as major newspapers and TV channels
have devoted many pages and prime-time shows to this development.
The People's Daily said in an editorial that carrying out the
strategy of developing western China is a major strategic choice
made by the government and this vast region will surely take on a
new look as a result of the consistent efforts of several
generations.
</P>
<P>
Democratic parties and non-governmental organizations also
strongly support this development. For example, at a coordination
meeting of local branches in 11 provinces, municipalities, and
autonomous regions, the China Democratic National Construction
Association (CDNCA) said that it will organize specialists among
its members to study and put forward suggestions for developing
the west, and pledged to supplement the government's effort to
carry out this strategy plan.
</P>
<P>
Minority ethnic groups may be the most enthusiastic about the
government plan, since most of them live in western China. Ismail
Amat, a state councilor from the Xinjiang Uygur Autonomous Region,
said that developing the west provides a historic opportunity for
minority ethnic groups to accelerate development.
</P>
<P>
He said that accelerating development of western China will not
only narrow the gap between eastern and western parts of the
country and consolidate unity among all ethnic groups, but will
also develop new growth areas for the national economy.
</P>
<P>
Local governments at all levels and relevant government
institutions have already began to coordinate their efforts to
implement the strategy for the development of the region.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE20000227.0170 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> People Enthusiastic about Development of Western China (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Chinese people from all walks
of life enthusiastically welcome and support the strategy the
Chinese government has adopted to develop the vast areas of
western China.
</P>
<P>
The government said recently that since the time is right, the
country will accelerate the development of western China to
invigorate the economy of the area, promote overall economic
growth, and realize the long-term goals of modernization.
</P>
<P>
Many corporations have expressed strong interest in the market
opportunities that are arising in the process of developing the
backward areas of west China.
</P>
<P>
The Xiyang Fireproof Material Company, a township enterprise in
northwest China's Liaoning Province, set up a 900-million-yuan
fertilizer factory in Guizhou Province in the southwest this month.
General manager Zhou Furen said that since Guizhou has rich
mineral resources such as phosphorous, his company is seizing the
first opportunity provided by government policy to tap into these
resources.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises in the east China coastal province of Zhejiang have
created scores of projects in western China, selling more than 100
billion yuan worth of goods and services in the area every year.
</P>
<P>
The All China Industry and Commerce Federation, the national
organization of non-government businesses, called for private
enterprises to push forward the industrialization of the farming
sector, tap into the mineral and tourism resources, and promote
the growth of trade and the service industry in the western region.
</P>
<P>
At the same time, the Chinese government has adopted measures
to facilitate investment in western China. According to the
Ministry of Railways, China will invest 100 million yuan in
railway construction in the region over the next five years, and
by the end of 2005, the total length of railways in this area will
increase to 18,000 kilometers.
</P>
<P>
Scientific and educational circles also have been quick to act.
The China Science and Technology Association, a national
organization of scientists, has decided to hold its annual meeting
in western China later this year, with the theme "Developing West
China--Science, Technology and Sustainable Development."
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
