<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Leicester to Keep Heskey Next Season  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, February 26 (Xinhua) -- Leicester City manager Martin O
'Neill has promised to "move heaven and earth" in a bid to keep
Emile Heskey at his club next season.
</P>
<P>
Despite continued speculation that Heskey will be leaving
Filbert Street this summer in a 10 million pounds move to Anfield,
Leicester boss O'Neill insists that no such deal has been done.
</P>
<P>
As he prepared for Sunday's Worthington Cup final against
Tranmere Rovers, O'Neill said he hoped to persuade Heskey to stay
at the club for at least another year.
</P>
<P>
"I'll move heaven and earth to try to keep Emile at Leicester
City Football Club," said O'Neill.
</P>
<P>
"I thought for a moment or two we might have lost him this time
last year, but we didn't. He stayed on and I'm hoping he might
give us at least another year again.
</P>
<P>
"I shall sit down and talk to him as soon as possible after the
Worthington Cup final, but the decision will eventually be down to
him.
</P>
<P>
"Emile is still only 22 years of age and he has had four
glorious years here. It is happening for him now and I am
delighted for him because he is a Leicester boy."
</P>
<P>
O'Neill rubbished suggestions that Heskey had already agreed to
join another club at the end of this season.
</P>
<P>
He said: "There is no legally binding deal with any other club.
The player is in pole position because he'll make the choice. We'
ll try to dissuade him but if he chooses to go then there is not a
great deal we can do about it.
</P>
<P>
"But we will do everything we can to keep him. Emile has put
himself right into the limelight after his performance for England
this week, but he did nothing at Wembley that I haven't seen
before.Obviously there will be plenty of speculation about him,
simply because of who he is and the fact that he plays for us, and
that everybody else is racing after him - there is phenomenal
interest in him," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
