<HEADLINE> Syrian FM Visits Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, February 27 (Xinhua) -- The talks between Saudi
Foreign Minister Saud Al-Faisal and his visiting Syrian counterpart
Faruk Shareh on Sunday affirmed both countries' common views on the
stalled Middle East peace process.
</P>
<P>
The Saudi Press Agency monitored here quoted Al-Faisal as saying
that Riyadh supports Syria, Lebanon and the Palestinians in their
efforts to regain all their legitimate rights.
</P>
<P>
The peace process ground to a halt as the escalation of fighting
between the Israeli occupation troops in south Lebanon and the
Iranian- and Syrian-backed Lebanese Hezbollah guerrillas. Israel
has launched massive air raids on Lebanese civilian targets, which
outraged the Arab world.
</P>
<P>
The situation in the Gulf region and means of promoting
bilateral relations in various fields between Saudi Arabia and
Syria were also discussed during the meeting, the report said.
</P>
<P>
The Syrian foreign minister conveyed Saudi Arabia's King Fahd
Ibn Abdul-Aziz the greetings of Syrian President Hafez Al-Assad.
</P>
<P>
Shareh arrived in Saudi Arabia earlier Sunday to attend the
session of the joint Saudi-Syrian committee co-chaired by him and
Al-Faisal. 
