<DATE_TIME> 2000-02-27 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Kenyan President in Egypt for COMESA Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Kenyan President Daniel arap
Moi received a red carpet welcome from Egyptian President Hosni
Mubarak when he arrived in Cairo on Sunday afternoon for a two-day
official visit, said the Kenyan Presidential Press Service.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Cairo, Moi will preside over the opening of
the two- day regional economic conference of the Common Market of
Eastern and Southern Africa (COMESA) which will begin Monday.
</P>
<P>
The conference, the first of its kind since Egypt joined the
COMESA in 1998, brings together the 18 member states of the
regional group.
</P>
<P>
Moi, as Chairman of the COMESA, will also preside over the
opening of a regional trade fair which will start March 1, just
immediately after the regional economic conference.
</P>
<P>
Kenya has sent a trade delegation to the COMESA trade fair in
Cairo as part of its market consolidation and expansion efforts
within the region which accounts for 44 percent of Kenya's
exports. 
</P>
</TEXT>
