<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Ethiopia Calls for International Help to Put out Forest Fire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, February 27 (Xinhua) -- Ethiopia on Sunday
appealed for international help to stop the fire from destroying
the forest in the south of the country.
</P>
<P>
Vice Minister of Agriculture Belay Ijigu told a press briefing
the appeal mainly focused on fire extinguishing operations with
chemicals as well as technical support.
</P>
<P>
The fire, which broke out 17 days ago, has been rampant in the
Bale and Borena regions, some 300 kilometers south of Addis Ababa,
having destroyed about 30,000 hectares of forests.
</P>
<P>
Prolonged dry season, windy weather and the rugged nature of
the topography were among the main factors exacerbating the fire,
according to the vice minister.
</P>
<P>
He said fire breaking structures were being constructed to stop
its advance fanned by gusty winds to the Bale Mountains National
Park and Lege Denbi gold mining suburbs.
</P>
<P>
A national committee was set up and over 5,000 people have
joined the efforts to snuff out the fire, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
